          "TITLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Experiments on Antiprotons: Cross Sections of Complex",
                "Nuclei"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "AUTHOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "L.E.Agnew",
                "O.Chamberlain",
                "D.V.Keller",
                "R.Mermod",
                "E.H.Rogers",
                "H.M.Steiner",
                "C.Wiegand"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "REFERENCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "code": "J,PR,108,1545,1957",
                "code_unit": [
                  {
                    "unit": "J,PR,108,1545,1957",
                    "doi": "10.1103/PhysRev.108.1545",
                    "field": {
                      "reference_type": "J",
                      "reference": {
                        "code": "PR",
                        "number": null,
                        "volume": "108",
                        "part": null,
                        "issue": null,
                        "page": "1545"
                      },
                      "date": 1957
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "unit_combination": "(%)"
              },
              "free_text": [
                "",
                "#doi:10.1103/PhysRev.108.1545"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INSTITUTE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "1USABRK",
                "1USAUCX"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "SYNCH"
                ],
                "institute": "1USABRK"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Bevatron, a weak-focusing proton",
                "synchrotron."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SPECT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The Bevatron beam incident upon the antiproton",
                "production target was in the energy range 5.8 to 6.3",
                "GeV. The internal beam intensity was from 2*10**10 to",
                "3*10**10 protons per pulse, one pulse every 6 seconds.",
                "The production targets used were C or (CH2)n."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SCIN",
                "CEREN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The velocity was determined by the use",
                "of Cherenkov counters that discriminated against pions",
                "but were sensitive to antiprotons. These counters",
                "consisted of liquid styrene radiators (index of",
                "refraction 1.543) viewed by one RCA-6810",
                "photomultiplier tube. The annihilation events were",
                "separately detected in Counter C*, which was a",
                "Cherenkov counter containing methyl alcohol (index of",
                "refraction 1.33)."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ASEP",
                "COINC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The mass spectrograph, which gave a",
                "signal whenever an antiproton passed through it. The",
                "spectrograph contained several improvements that",
                "greatly increased the luminosity of the apparatus.",
                "This was accomplished by increasing the aperture of",
                "the spectroscope and, also, by accepting a momentum",
                "interval of 3% instead of only 1% as before. This",
                "relaxation of the momentum definition made the mass",
                "determination less precise, but once antiprotons had",
                "been identified, we could afford this uncertainty.",
                "Nuclear-emulsion studies of annihilations of",
                "antiprotons have shown that nearly all annihilations",
                "give rise to fast charged pions (fast enough to give",
                "detectable light in methyl alcohol) or neutral pions",
                " (whose gamma rays frequently are converted within",
                "Counter C* and give detectable Cherenkov radiation).",
                "Each antiproton indicated by the mass spectrograph",
                "was considered an annihilation if it was accompanied",
                "by a pulse in the C* counter, irrespective of whether",
                "counts were registered by other counters. If no pulse",
                "was seen in the C* counter, then the presence or",
                "absence of pulses in other counters indicated whether",
                "the antiproton in question passed through without",
                "scattering (actually, scattered to an angle smaller",
                "than 14.3 degrees), or scattered to an angle between",
                "14.3 and 20.5 degrees, or scattered to an angle",
                "greater than 20.5 degrees."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-S",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The statistical errors in the determination",
                "of the cross sections are given by the formula dsigma",
                "thetac = (1/N)*[(1/(I thetac))-(1/(I0)) ]**0.5,",
                "where N is the thickness of the absorber in the slots",
                "in nuclei per square centimeter, I0 the number of",
                "incident particles, I thetac is the number of",
                "pass-through particles with a cutoff angle thetac.",
                "Some other systematic error will be shown by further",
                "experiments."
              ]
            }
          ],
